This paper is about action localization, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a new baseline model for the AVA dataset, which involves adapting the Faster R-CNN framework and using spatiotemporal features produced by an I3D model pretrained on Kinetics. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as well as multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) due to the potential applications of action localization in these fields.
